						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up near the Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1548 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1470, Kīlaka, Vaīśākha śu. 11</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1548 A.D., April 18, (Wednesday).</hi></p>						

						<p>Seems to record a gift of land in Ālaguvāṭa in Penna-māṅgāṇi in Pennakacherlasīma, of Jagatāpi-Gutti, to god Rāmēśvara of the village by Mūrtirāju Rāmayyadēva-mahārāju who is said to have been ruling Pennakacherla-sīma.</p>						

						</summary>
